In my judgment, the husband’s figure for non-matrimonial property (c.£6.5 million

 see para 70
	      ) is a broadly accurate assessment of the value of his post-separation endeavour.  As I have said, there is no serious challenge from the wife to the calculation of his post-separation earnings.  The wife’s entitlement to claim any part of the value of these assets must thus be based upon a legitimate needs-based claim.  No one in this case is suggesting that there is a solid Miller compensation claim in this case over and above a full assessment of her future needs.
